UNITED STATES, Plaintiff In Error, v. MARYLAND CASUALTY CO., Defendant in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 27, 1929. No. 5355. Geo. J. Hatfield, U. S. Atty., and Geo. M. Naus, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal. John Ralph Wilson, of San Francisco, Cal. (Everette C. McKeage, of San Francisco, Cal., of counsel), for defendant in error.

Before GILBERT, RUDKIN, and DIETRICH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Reversed, on authority of United States v. John Barth Co. and United States Fidelity & Guaranty Co., 49 S. Ct. 366, 73 L. Ed.-, decided by the Supreme Court May 13, 1929.
